{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17642749","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17642749"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T19:43:39+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T19:43:39+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17960"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17960","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17960"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.06,0.15,0.4,0.13,0.27]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10674"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78861"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10674","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10674"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17960"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64210"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4927"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"6746"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"24862"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24866"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27059"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78861","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/78861"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe paranasal sinuses have a number of functions.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is NOT a function of the paranasal sinuses?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Contribute to vocal resonance","Decrease the weight of the skull","Filter inhaled air","Humidify and heat inhaled air","Insulate against rapid temperature changes"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe paranasal sinuses have several functions. They help to \u003Cstrong\u003Ehumidify and heat inhaled air\u003C/strong\u003E, which is important for maintaining the moisture and temperature of the air reaching the lungs. They also \u003Cstrong\u003Econtribute to vocal resonance\u003C/strong\u003E, enhancing the quality of the voice. Additionally, the sinuses \u003Cstrong\u003Edecrease the weight of the skull\u003C/strong\u003E, making it easier for the head to be supported by the neck. They also \u003Cstrong\u003Einsulate against rapid temperature changes\u003C/strong\u003E, protecting the brain from sudden shifts in temperature.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHowever, the sinuses do not \u003Cstrong\u003Efilter inhaled air\u003C/strong\u003E. This function is primarily performed by the nasal passages and the mucociliary apparatus within the respiratory tract, which trap and remove particles and pathogens from the air before it reaches the lungs.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The paranasal sinuses have several functions including humidifying and heating inhaled air, contributing to vocal resonance, decreasing the weight of the skull, and insulating against rapid temperature changes."],"references":["Singh, V. (2023). Textbook of Anatomy-Head, Neck and Brain, Volume III-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Patestas, M. A., \u0026 Gartner, L. P. (2016). A textbook of neuroanatomy. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Patel, C. R., Fernandez-Miranda, J. C., Wang, W. H., \u0026 Wang, E. W. (2016). Skull Base Anatomy. Otolaryngologic clinics of North America, 49(1), 9\u201320. https://doi.org/10.1016/j.otc.2015.09.001","Anderson, B. W., Kortz, M. W., Black, A. C., \u0026 Al Kharazi, K. A. (2023). Anatomy, Head and Neck, Skull. In StatPearls. StatPearls Publishing"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64210"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17960"}},"stem